We faced the same issue earlier when calling Google Address Validation API directly from our service. The request was getting blocked by corporate proxy/security policies, even after configuring proxy in the application.

The working approach we adopted was to avoid calling Google API directly and instead use the existing wrapper service via Provider Connect, which already handles Trillium + Google calls and required authentication.

This removed the need for additional proxy handling and whitelisting from our side, and resolved the issue.
